<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>MadeMy IT Solutions</title><link>https://mademy.nl/en/</link><description>Recent content on MadeMy IT Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Fri, 24 Apr 2026 00:16:58 +0200</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://mademy.nl/en/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Telecom Provider - From Manual to Automated</title><link>https://mademy.nl/en/usecases/telecom-provider-migratie/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mademy.nl/en/usecases/telecom-provider-migratie/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Hosting Provider - From Hyper-V to Open Source</title><link>https://mademy.nl/en/usecases/hosting-provider-migratie/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mademy.nl/en/usecases/hosting-provider-migratie/</guid><description/></item><item><title>IT Service Provider - From VMware to Proxmox VE</title><link>https://mademy.nl/en/usecases/it-dienstverlener-vmware-migratie/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mademy.nl/en/usecases/it-dienstverlener-vmware-migratie/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Software Company - Local AI Infrastructure</title><link>https://mademy.nl/en/usecases/softwarebedrijf-ai-infrastructuur/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mademy.nl/en/usecases/softwarebedrijf-ai-infrastructuur/</guid><description/></item><item><title>VMware vSphere Foundation: What are the alternatives?</title><link>https://mademy.nl/en/blog/vmware-alternatives/</link><pubDate>Tue, 21 Apr 2026 10:00:00 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://mademy.nl/en/blog/vmware-alternatives/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="vmware-vsphere-foundation-what-are-the-alternatives"&gt;VMware vSphere Foundation: What are the alternatives?&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After Broadcom discontinued perpetual licences and introduced the subscription model, many customers were already unpleasantly surprised. On top of licences becoming significantly more expensive, Broadcom has once again tightened its licensing model. It is now even only possible to purchase a VMware vSphere Foundation subscription for a maximum of one year. Understandably, companies fear that subscription costs will rise sharply after the first year. And if you don&amp;rsquo;t pay, you simply lose the ability to manage your VMs, you can&amp;rsquo;t even power them on or off.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Proxmox Installation: The Complete Step-by-Step Guide</title><link>https://mademy.nl/en/blog/proxmox-installation/</link><pubDate>Thu, 15 Feb 2024 10:00:00 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://mademy.nl/en/blog/proxmox-installation/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="proxmox-installation-the-complete-step-by-step-guide"&gt;Proxmox Installation: The Complete Step-by-Step Guide&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Proxmox VE is a powerful virtualization platform, but how do you get started? In this guide, we walk you through a complete installation and basic configuration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="hardware-requirements"&gt;Hardware Requirements&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="minimum-requirements"&gt;Minimum Requirements&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CPU&lt;/strong&gt;: 64-bit processor with VT-x/AMD-V&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RAM&lt;/strong&gt;: 4GB (8GB+ recommended)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Storage&lt;/strong&gt;: 32GB available space&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Network&lt;/strong&gt;: 1Gbps NIC&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id="recommended-for-production"&gt;Recommended for Production&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CPU&lt;/strong&gt;: Dual socket server grade&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RAM&lt;/strong&gt;: 64GB+ ECC RAM&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Storage&lt;/strong&gt;: SSD/NVMe for OS, separate storage pool&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Network&lt;/strong&gt;: 10Gbps+, redundant&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="step-1-iso-download"&gt;Step 1: ISO Download&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Go to &lt;a href="https://proxmox.com"&gt;proxmox.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Download the latest ISO (currently 8.1)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create a bootable USB stick with Rufus (Windows) or dd (Linux)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;div style="background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;
&lt;table style="border-spacing:0;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;"&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style="vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;;width:100%"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#57606a"&gt;# Linux command for USB stick&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo dd &lt;span style="color:#cf222e"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#0550ae"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;proxmox-ve_8.1.iso &lt;span style="color:#953800"&gt;of&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#0550ae"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;/dev/sdX &lt;span style="color:#953800"&gt;bs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#0550ae"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;4M &lt;span style="color:#953800"&gt;status&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#0550ae"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;progress
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="step-2-installation"&gt;Step 2: Installation&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="boot-from-usb"&gt;Boot from USB&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Insert USB stick into server&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Boot from USB (F11/F12 for boot menu)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Select &amp;ldquo;Install Proxmox VE&amp;rdquo;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h3 id="installation-wizard"&gt;Installation Wizard&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4 id="language-selection"&gt;Language Selection&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Choose your language (English recommended for troubleshooting)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4 id="eula"&gt;EULA&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accept the license agreement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4 id="target-harddisk"&gt;Target Harddisk&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Select the disk for Proxmox installation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tip&lt;/strong&gt;: Use a separate disk (not the storage disks)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4 id="country--timezone"&gt;Country &amp;amp; Timezone&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Country: Netherlands&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Timezone: Europe/Amsterdam&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keyboard: Dutch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4 id="administrator-password"&gt;Administrator Password&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enter a strong password&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write this down carefully!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4 id="network-configuration"&gt;Network Configuration&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hostname&lt;/strong&gt;: pve01.yourdomain.local&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IP Address&lt;/strong&gt;: Static IP (e.g. 192.168.1.10)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Netmask&lt;/strong&gt;: 255.255.255.0&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gateway&lt;/strong&gt;: 192.168.1.1&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DNS&lt;/strong&gt;: 8.8.8.8, 1.1.1.1&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="step-3-first-login"&gt;Step 3: First Login&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After installation, you can log in via:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Best Practices for Windows VMs in Proxmox VE</title><link>https://mademy.nl/en/blog/windows-vm-best-practices/</link><pubDate>Thu, 01 Feb 2024 10:00:00 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://mademy.nl/en/blog/windows-vm-best-practices/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="best-practices-for-windows-vms-in-proxmox-ve"&gt;Best Practices for Windows VMs in Proxmox VE&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Windows VMs run excellently on Proxmox VE, but there are some optimizations that significantly improve performance and stability. In this article, we share our experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="vm-hardware-configuration"&gt;VM Hardware Configuration&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="cpu"&gt;CPU&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4 id="cpu-type"&gt;CPU Type&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Choose &lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;host&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt; as CPU type for best performance:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0"&gt;&lt;code&gt;Hardware → Processors → Type: host
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;This gives the VM access to all CPU features of the host.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id="cores-vs-sockets"&gt;Cores vs Sockets&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Windows Desktop: 1 socket, 2-8 cores&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Windows Server: 1-2 sockets, 4-16 cores&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Important&lt;/strong&gt;: Windows licenses are socket-based&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id="memory"&gt;Memory&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4 id="ballooning"&gt;Ballooning&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Disable memory ballooning for stable performance:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Agentic AI</title><link>https://mademy.nl/en/diensten/artificial-intelligence/agentic-ai/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mademy.nl/en/diensten/artificial-intelligence/agentic-ai/</guid><description/></item><item><title>AI Agent</title><link>https://mademy.nl/en/diensten/artificial-intelligence/ai-agent/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mademy.nl/en/diensten/artificial-intelligence/ai-agent/</guid><description/></item><item><title>AI Consulting</title><link>https://mademy.nl/en/diensten/artificial-intelligence/advies/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mademy.nl/en/diensten/artificial-intelligence/advies/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Colocation</title><link>https://mademy.nl/en/diensten/hosting/colocatie/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mademy.nl/en/diensten/hosting/colocatie/</guid><description/></item><item><title>EU Cloud</title><link>https://mademy.nl/en/diensten/hosting/eu-cloud/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mademy.nl/en/diensten/hosting/eu-cloud/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Licenses</title><link>https://mademy.nl/en/diensten/hardware-software/licenties/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mademy.nl/en/diensten/hardware-software/licenties/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Local LLMs</title><link>https://mademy.nl/en/diensten/artificial-intelligence/local-llms/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mademy.nl/en/diensten/artificial-intelligence/local-llms/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Privacy Policy</title><link>https://mademy.nl/en/privacy-policy/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mademy.nl/en/privacy-policy/</guid><description>&lt;h1 i